translated: Klint, Bo Axel Duse, major, Skövde, b. 27/4/07 in Stockholm to PhD Axel K. and Karin Duse. Married 35 years to Ingrid Julin. Children: Ann Mari b. 37, Barbro b. 40, Carin b. 43, Dagmar b. 47. Education: graduated from Norra real school in Stockholm in 1925, officer's exam in 1927, AlliSak in 1932, AIHShk in 1934, ArtSS in 1936, InfSS in 1942. Military service: second lieutenant in the fortification corps in 1928, lieutenant in 1932, lieutenant in S.l in 1937, captain in 1939, captain in the general staff in 1940, captain in the 1.4 regiment in 1944, major in 1946, serving with the general staff same year. Served in the Engineering 2 from 1925-26, Engineering 1 in 1926, Engineering 3 from 1928-37, engineering staff in Boden in 1934, fortification headquarters from 1936-37, 1.2 in 1936, repeater at AIHS from 1936-38, S.l from 1937-38, defense staff from 1938-43, LKE in 1939, army staff in 1940, 4th military district from 1943-44, 1.4 from 1944-46, 3rd military district since 1946, staff chief there since 1947. Involved in the development of various military regulations and instructions from 1940-43, collaborator in several professional journals, among others, from 1938-44. Travelled to Germany, Austria, and Italy in 1921, Denmark in 1921 and 1932, Norway in 1928, 1930, and 1935, Finland in 1932. Awarded RSO (Order of the Sword), SkytteM (Shooting Medal), and Pistol Shooting Association national championship medals.
